00:25:04.320 --> 00:25:06.870
In 10 years.

00:25:06.870 --> 00:25:11.950
Folks, I used to count to
four and rhyme for a living.

00:25:11.950 --> 00:25:13.870
That was music.

00:25:13.870 --> 00:25:18.960
When you reach out and you
take a step towards your riot,

00:25:18.960 --> 00:25:22.080
you have no idea what
you're capable of.

00:25:22.080 --> 00:25:26.160
You have no idea how
powerful your how

00:25:26.160 --> 00:25:28.740
operates in this world.

00:25:28.740 --> 00:25:31.290
That is how you find
purpose, by taking

00:25:31.290 --> 00:25:35.640
on the problems of others who
can not ever possibly pay you

00:25:35.640 --> 00:25:38.300
back.

00:25:38.300 --> 00:25:42.161
I want to talk about
how to find your riot.

00:25:42.161 --> 00:25:43.660
You know, we hear
this all the time.

00:25:43.660 --> 00:25:45.609
It's like, that's great,
find your purpose,

00:25:45.609 --> 00:25:46.400
all the rest of it.

00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:48.620
Not very many
people give us a way

00:25:48.620 --> 00:25:50.900
in which we can take
a step towards that.

00:25:50.900 --> 00:25:58.900
And I want to introduce you
to someone who, to me, just

00:25:58.900 --> 00:26:00.847
lives finding a riot
better than anyone else.

00:26:00.847 --> 00:26:02.680
It's probably someone
you've never heard of.

00:26:02.680 --> 00:26:04.810
Her name is Alice
Harris, and she grew up

00:26:04.810 --> 00:26:06.700
in the late 19th century.

00:26:06.700 --> 00:26:12.250
And her dream-- her dream was
to be a missionary to Africa.

00:26:12.250 --> 00:26:15.140
She met a man,
John, and they got

00:26:15.140 --> 00:26:19.140
sent to what was then the free
state of Congo, which happened

00:26:19.140 --> 00:26:22.240
to be a territory in Africa
that was not yet colonized,

00:26:22.240 --> 00:26:26.930
one of the largest territories
in Africa around 1900.

00:26:26.930 --> 00:26:30.740
And there they did their
missionary work, very noble

00:26:30.740 --> 00:26:31.361
work.

00:26:31.361 --> 00:26:33.110
Actually, it was a
part of a larger system

00:26:33.110 --> 00:26:35.060
because at the time
there was a lot of work

00:26:35.060 --> 00:26:37.070
to be able to help
educate and bring science

00:26:37.070 --> 00:26:41.790
to the region, which actually
turned out to be a ploy.

00:26:41.790 --> 00:26:43.040
But they were doing their bit.

00:26:43.040 --> 00:26:44.664
They were doing what
they were good at,

00:26:44.664 --> 00:26:47.070
and they were doing their
life the way they saw fit.

00:26:47.070 --> 00:26:48.580
And one day when John
was away on business,

00:26:48.580 --> 00:26:49.730
her husband was
away on business--

00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:50.770
they had no children.

00:26:50.770 --> 00:26:54.220
When John was away on business
one of the local tribes-people

00:26:54.220 --> 00:26:58.097
came to her door and said,
I really want to see you.

00:26:58.097 --> 00:26:59.430
I want to see you, specifically.

00:26:59.430 --> 00:27:01.140
His name was Nasala.

00:27:01.140 --> 00:27:04.140
And Nasala came up and said,
I have something to show you.

00:27:07.402 --> 00:27:09.860
And she came and he set it out
and he brought this plantain

00:27:09.860 --> 00:27:11.900
leaf, and he set it
out onto her veranda.

00:27:11.900 --> 00:27:15.590
He's like, I need you
to see what's happening.

00:27:15.590 --> 00:27:18.490
And so she walked
up and it's really--

00:27:18.490 --> 00:27:19.470
let me go back here.

00:27:22.130 --> 00:27:24.310
As she came upon the
open plantain leaf

00:27:24.310 --> 00:27:28.060
that Nasala brought she realized
that it was the severed hand

00:27:28.060 --> 00:27:29.710
and foot of his daughter.

00:27:33.130 --> 00:27:36.680
I'm going to stop there and
tell you why that happened.

00:27:36.680 --> 00:27:39.630
See, over in Belgium
there was this mad King

00:27:39.630 --> 00:27:41.850
called King Leopold II.

00:27:41.850 --> 00:27:45.170
And he was very jealous of all
the other leaders in Europe

00:27:45.170 --> 00:27:49.020
because everyone else got to
colonize Africa and he didn't.

00:27:49.020 --> 00:27:51.470
And actually, colonization
at this point in history--

00:27:51.470 --> 00:27:53.150
people were starting
to look down on it.

00:27:53.150 --> 00:27:55.640
Slavery is kind of illegal-ish.

00:27:55.640 --> 00:27:58.310
And so he had to figure out a
way to get his own land grab.

00:27:58.310 --> 00:28:00.650
So he created a
company, basically

00:28:00.650 --> 00:28:03.260
an institute, that was able
to go in and quote unquote,

00:28:03.260 --> 00:28:06.995
"bring science and education"
to this entire region.

00:28:06.995 --> 00:28:09.230
But what it really
was was a ploy

00:28:09.230 --> 00:28:12.290
to be able to start pulling
out the natural resources that

00:28:12.290 --> 00:28:13.520
were in the Congo.

00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:17.660
And he named it the Free State
of Congo, believe it or not.

00:28:17.660 --> 00:28:20.310
And what he did was he set up a
police force called the "Force

00:28:20.310 --> 00:28:24.950
Publique" who would
go out and take land

00:28:24.950 --> 00:28:26.840
from local tribes-people
and then force

00:28:26.840 --> 00:28:27.810
them to work the land.

00:28:27.810 --> 00:28:29.090
And, in fact, what
they were really

00:28:29.090 --> 00:28:31.190
finding was-- one of the
hottest commodities that

00:28:31.190 --> 00:28:33.800
was coming out of Congo
at this time was rubber.

00:28:33.800 --> 00:28:35.990
And rubber was in big
demand because bike tires

00:28:35.990 --> 00:28:38.540
and automobiles were just
really getting started.

00:28:38.540 --> 00:28:40.910
And basically what
Leopold was doing

00:28:40.910 --> 00:28:43.910
was creating this illicit
business in slavery

00:28:43.910 --> 00:28:46.430
and just making a fortune.

00:28:46.430 --> 00:28:49.590
But he was a total cheapskate.

00:28:49.590 --> 00:28:51.450
Total cheapskate.

00:28:51.450 --> 00:28:54.720
He wanted an accounting
of every single bullet

00:28:54.720 --> 00:28:56.220
that his force used.

00:28:56.220 --> 00:28:57.240
So he required them--

00:28:57.240 --> 00:28:58.740
because he was
afraid that they were

00:28:58.740 --> 00:29:01.323
going to go out and use bullets
to go hunt game for themselves

00:29:01.323 --> 00:29:02.287
and whatnot.

00:29:02.287 --> 00:29:04.620
So what he required-- if
you're going to shoot a bullet,

00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:06.900
I need to see a hand
or a foot to prove

00:29:06.900 --> 00:29:09.139
that you killed someone.

00:29:09.139 --> 00:29:11.180
And the Force Publique
got kind of smart about it

00:29:11.180 --> 00:29:12.990
and so they figured, well, let's
just get ahead of the game.

00:29:12.990 --> 00:29:15.120
Let's go hack off hands
and feet and get ahead.

00:29:15.120 --> 00:29:16.786
That way our accounting
system will work

00:29:16.786 --> 00:29:19.180
when we come back at the end.

00:29:19.180 --> 00:29:22.370
And that's how you
get Nasala's story.

00:29:22.370 --> 00:29:26.240
So here Alice is looking at
what's happening on her door,

00:29:26.240 --> 00:29:30.920
on that veranda, on those
steps, in that moment

00:29:30.920 --> 00:29:32.630
she found her riot.

00:29:32.630 --> 00:29:33.920
She found her purpose.

00:29:33.920 --> 00:29:35.210
And here's the takeaway.

00:29:35.210 --> 00:29:36.800
This is what she did.

00:29:36.800 --> 00:29:39.830
She walked back inside, she
grabbed the coolest thing

00:29:39.830 --> 00:29:44.310
she had, which was a Kodak
brownie camera, which

00:29:44.310 --> 00:29:47.200
was the coolest piece of tech
you could have at the time,

00:29:47.200 --> 00:29:52.007
and it was affordable,
that she took that picture.

00:29:52.007 --> 00:29:52.840
I'll show you again.

00:29:57.340 --> 00:29:59.900
And she didn't stop there.

00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:02.920
She went on taking
more and more pictures.

00:30:02.920 --> 00:30:05.020
And she started documenting
the atrocities that

00:30:05.020 --> 00:30:07.270
were happening all over Congo.

00:30:07.270 --> 00:30:09.552
No one else was doing
this at the time.

00:30:09.552 --> 00:30:13.560
And she realized that something
inside of her was happening.

00:30:13.560 --> 00:30:15.960
Guess what she didn't do?

00:30:15.960 --> 00:30:19.260
She didn't ask
anyone's permission.

00:30:19.260 --> 00:30:21.090
Don't you think
you'd want permission

00:30:21.090 --> 00:30:24.150
to go try to take down
a European leader?

00:30:24.150 --> 00:30:25.710
That sounds like
something you would

00:30:25.710 --> 00:30:28.790
want to call in a professional
for, or get something

00:30:28.790 --> 00:30:33.920
a little bit bigger than a
demure missionary from England.

00:30:33.920 --> 00:30:35.310
But she kept going.

00:30:35.310 --> 00:30:37.650
And then she realized, in
order to get the word out--

00:30:37.650 --> 00:30:40.606
because Leopold was fighting her
left and right in the papers,

00:30:40.606 --> 00:30:42.230
keeping her pictures
from getting out--

00:30:42.230 --> 00:30:43.530
so she said forget it.

00:30:43.530 --> 00:30:45.180
I'm going to go
on a magic lantern

00:30:45.180 --> 00:30:49.960
tour-- which is essentially the
1900s version of PowerPoint.

00:30:49.960 --> 00:30:52.752
And she took her pictures
all around America, all

00:30:52.752 --> 00:30:54.210
around England,
and started getting

00:30:54.210 --> 00:30:57.330
the attention of Mark
Twain and the president

00:30:57.330 --> 00:31:01.860
and the Queen of England with
a very short amount of time.

00:31:01.860 --> 00:31:03.930
His entire reign was
shut down, and he

00:31:03.930 --> 00:31:09.240
was no longer able to
exploit the people of Congo.

00:31:09.240 --> 00:31:14.190
This one woman found her
riot, and took a step,

00:31:14.190 --> 00:31:18.870
and was able to change an entire
system, a poverty of means,

00:31:18.870 --> 00:31:22.770
purely because she was
able to do something

00:31:22.770 --> 00:31:25.080
without permission.

00:31:25.080 --> 00:31:27.477
So the takeaway that
I give you today

00:31:27.477 --> 00:31:29.060
is that, when you
look for your riot--

00:31:29.060 --> 00:31:32.090
my right is obviously
human trafficking.

00:31:32.090 --> 00:31:34.984
Our riots don't need to
be in a faraway place.

00:31:34.984 --> 00:31:36.650
Your riot-- the thing
that could bug you

00:31:36.650 --> 00:31:38.870
is the fact that not enough
kids in your neighborhood

00:31:38.870 --> 00:31:41.129
have parents helping
them with their homework

00:31:41.129 --> 00:31:43.670
because they all work and have
two jobs and they're too busy.

00:31:43.670 --> 00:31:45.440
That's a riot.

00:31:45.440 --> 00:31:47.590
It doesn't have to be
something this big.

00:31:47.590 --> 00:31:49.270
And if it's a thing
that bothers you,

00:31:49.270 --> 00:31:51.100
if it's a thing inside
of you that says,

00:31:51.100 --> 00:31:55.490
I wish the world was this
way, I want to challenge you.

00:31:55.490 --> 00:31:58.140
You might be the one to fix it.

00:31:58.140 --> 00:32:01.560
She could have left Nasala
on the porch and said,

00:32:01.560 --> 00:32:02.670
I'm so sorry.

00:32:02.670 --> 00:32:04.910
I'll go write a letter.

00:32:04.910 --> 00:32:06.320
I'll do what I can.

00:32:06.320 --> 00:32:09.260
Instead, she grabbed
what she already had,

00:32:09.260 --> 00:32:12.590
the talent and the skills
and the possessions

00:32:12.590 --> 00:32:15.870
that she already had, and
started working on it.

00:32:15.870 --> 00:32:19.640
Anyone-- anyone in here
can find their riot

00:32:19.640 --> 00:32:23.040
and act on it as long as they
don't ask permission and just

00:32:23.040 --> 00:32:26.310
choose to use what
you already have.

00:32:26.310 --> 00:32:31.580
When Dr. King gave his
message at Oberlin College

00:32:31.580 --> 00:32:33.560
he spoke to this
need for meaning.

00:32:33.560 --> 00:32:39.560
He called it an inescapable
network of mutuality.

00:32:39.560 --> 00:32:43.160
And he said that, I am not who
I am supposed to be until you

00:32:43.160 --> 00:32:44.834
are who you're supposed to be.

00:32:44.834 --> 00:32:46.250
And you're not who
you're supposed

00:32:46.250 --> 00:32:48.860
to be until the
person next to you

00:32:48.860 --> 00:32:50.690
is who they're supposed to be.

00:32:50.690 --> 00:32:53.480
And in a global village
like we live in today,

00:32:53.480 --> 00:32:58.370
that axiom is true
on a global scale.

00:32:58.370 --> 00:33:01.120
We actually find ourselves
when we give ourselves

00:33:01.120 --> 00:33:05.710
away to people's problems
who can never pay us back.

00:33:05.710 --> 00:33:08.710
That is your path
to purpose, and that

00:33:08.710 --> 00:33:10.145
is how you find your riot.

00:33:10.145 --> 00:33:12.520
And I want to thank you all
for letting me have this time

00:33:12.520 --> 00:33:13.436
to be able to do this.

00:33:13.436 --> 00:33:14.314
Thank you so much.

00:33:14.314 --> 00:33:17.158
